<EFX_PART_I>
<A NAME="FIS_PART_I"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART I
</FONT>
<A NAME="PCCC-20151231X10K_HTM_PARTI_156521">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Business
</FONT>
<A NAME="PCCC-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1BUSINESS_538779">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	GENERAL
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	national solutions provider
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of a wide range of information technology, or IT, solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;We help
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	design, enable, manage, and service their IT environments. We provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, including computer systems, software and peripheral equipment, networking communications, and other products and accessories that we purchase from manufacturers, distributors, and other suppliers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	services involving
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	design, configuration, and implementation of IT solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;These services are performed by our personnel and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	third-party providers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	operating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	segments, which serve primarily: (a) small- to medium-sized businesses, or SMBs,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in our SMB segment,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	through our PC Connection Sales subsidiary, (b) large enterprise customers, in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Large Account
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, through our MoreDirect subsidiar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(c) federal, state, and local government and educational institutions, in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Public Sector
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, through our GovConnection subsidiary.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We generate sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	through (i)&nbsp;outbound telemarketing and field sales contacts by sales representatives focused on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	business, education
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	al
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	healthcare,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and government markets, (ii)&nbsp;our
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	2

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	government and education

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	al
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	institutions

	IT

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The largest segment of this market is served by local and regional &#x201C;value added resellers,&#x201D; or VARs, many of whom we believe are transitioning from the hardware and software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products

	business to

</FONT>

	ing

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	SERVICE AND SUPPORT

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Since our founding in 1982, our primary objective has been to provide products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and support
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We invest in training programs for our service and support personnel, with an emphasis on putting customer needs and service first.&nbsp;&nbsp;Product support technicians assist callers with questions concerning compatibility, installation, and more difficult questions relating to product use.&nbsp;&nbsp;The product support technicians authorize customers to return defective or incompatible products to either the manufacturer or to us for warranty service.&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Using our customized information system, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	transmit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our customer orders either to our distribution center or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our drop
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ship suppliers, depending on product availability, for processing immediately after a customer receives credit approval.&nbsp;&nbsp;At our distribution center, we also perform custom configuration of computer systems as requested by our customers, which typically consists of the installation of memory, accessories, and/or software purchased.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our customers may select the method of delivery that best meets their needs and is most cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	effective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,

	ranging from expedited overnight delivery for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our inventory stocking levels are based on three primary criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;First, we stock and maintain a large quantity of products that sell through quickly (such as notebook and desktop systems, printers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and monitors).&nbsp;&nbsp;Second, we stock products obtained through opportunistic purchases (including first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;market and end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;life special promotions, and popular products with limited availability).&nbsp;&nbsp;Third, we stock products in common demand, such as components we use to configure systems prior to shipping, for which we want to avoid shortages.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory stocking decisions are made generally independent of the level of shipping service, as expedited shipping, including overnight delivery, is available through the majority of our drop
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ship suppliers as well as through our warehouse.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Outbound Telemarketing and Field Sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;We seek to build loyal relationships with potential high-volume customers by assigning them to individual account managers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that customers respond favorably to one-on-one relationship
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with personalized, well-trained account managers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once established, these one-on-one relationships are maintained and enhanced through frequent telecommunications and targeted catalogs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and e-mails, as well as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	other marketing materials designed to meet each customer&#x2019;s specific IT needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We pay most of our account managers a base annual salary plus incentive compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Incentive compensation is tied to gross profit dollars produced by the individual account manager.&nbsp;&nbsp;Account managers historically have significantly increased productivity after approximately twelve months of training and experience.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Through our MoreDirect subsidiary&#x2019;s custom designed Web-based system, we are able to offer our larger corporate customers an efficient and effective method of sourcing, evaluating, purchasing, and tracking a wide variety of IT products and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;MoreDirect&#x2019;s strategy is to be the primary single source procurement portal for its large corporate customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;MoreDirect&#x2019;s sales representatives typically have ten to twenty years of experience and are located strategically across the United States.&nbsp;&nbsp;This allows them to work directly with customers, often on site.&nbsp;&nbsp;MoreDirect generally places its product orders with manufacturers and/or distribution companies for drop shipment directly to its customers.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	product

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We fulfill orders from customers both from products we hold in inventory and through drop shipping arrangements with manufacturers and distributors.&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>

	hrough our Everything Overnight

	&#xAE;

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 1A.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Risk Factors
</FONT>
<A NAME="PCCC-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1ARISKFACTORS_401906">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We cannot assure investors that our assumptions and expectations will prove to have been correct.&nbsp;&nbsp;Important factors could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated or implied by forward-looking statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such factors that could cause or contribute to such differences include those factors discussed below.&nbsp;&nbsp;We undertake no intention or obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	or otherwise.&nbsp;&nbsp;If any of the following risks actually occur, our business, financial condition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	or results of operations would likely suffer.

	nstability in

	uently on our financial results

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	results also may vary based on our ability to manage personnel levels in response to fluctuations in revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;We base personnel levels and other operating expenditures on sales forecasts.&nbsp;&nbsp;If our revenues do not meet anticipated levels in the future, we may not be able to reduce our staffing levels and operating expenses in a timely manner to avoid significant losses from operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Substantial competition could reduce our market share and may negatively affect our business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The direct marketing industry and the computer products retail business, in particular, are highly competitive.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We compete with other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	national solutions provider
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s of hardware and software and computer related products, including CDW Corporation and Insight Enterprises, Inc.,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	each of which is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	much larger than we are.&nbsp;&nbsp;Certain hardware and software vendors, such as Apple, Dell, Lenovo, and HP, who provide products to us, also sell their products directly to end users through their own catalogs, stores, and via the Internet.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	also
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	compete with computer retail stores
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and websites, who are increasingly selling to business customers and may become a significant competitor.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We compete not only for customers, but also for advertising support from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	product manufacturers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some of our competitors have larger customer bases and greater financial, marketing, and other resources than we do.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, some of our competitors offer a wider range of products and services than we do and may be able to respond more quickly to new or changing opportunities, technologies, and customer requirements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many current and potential competitors also have greater name recognition, engage in more extensive promotional activities, and adopt pricing policies that are more aggressive than ours.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect competition to increase as retailers and direct marketers who have not traditionally sold computers and related products enter the industry.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, product resellers and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	national solutions provider
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s are combining operations or acquiring or merging with other resellers and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	national solutions provider
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s to increase efficiency.&nbsp;&nbsp;Moreover, current and potential competitors have established or may establish cooperative relationships among themselves or with third parties to enhance their products and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, it is possible that new competitors or alliances among competitors may emerge and acquire significant market share.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may not be able to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	continue to compete effectively against our current or future competitors.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we encounter new competition or fail to compete effectively against our competitors, our business may be harmed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	We face and will continue to face significant price competition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Generally, pricing is very aggressive in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	industry, and we expect pricing pressures to escalate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	should
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	economic conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	deteriorate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;An increase in price competition could result in a reduction of our profit margins.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We may not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be able to offset the effects of price reductions with an increase in the number of customers, higher sales, cost reductions, or otherwise.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, our sales of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	hardware products generally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	result in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	lower profit margins than those associated with software products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such pricing pressures could result in an erosion of our market share, reduced sales, and reduced operating margins, any of which could have a material adverse effect on our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Virtualization of IT resources and applications, including networks, servers, applications, and data storage may disrupt or alter our traditional distribution models.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our customers can access, through a cloud-based platform, business-critical solutions without the significant initial capital investment required for dedicated infrastructure.&nbsp;&nbsp;Growing demand for the development of cloud-based solutions may reduce demand for some of our existing hardware products.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the transition to an environment
</FONT>

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Many product suppliers provide us with advertising allowances, and in exchange, we feature their products in our catalogs and other marketing vehicles.&nbsp;&nbsp;These vendor allowances, to the extent that they represent specific reimbursements of incremental and identifiable costs, are offset against SG&amp;A expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Advertising allowances that cannot be associated with a specific program funded by an individual vendor or that exceed the fair value of advertising expense associated with that program are classified as offsets to cost of sales or inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the past, we have experienced a decrease in the level of vendor consideration available to us from certain manufacturers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The level of such consideration we receive from some manufacturers may decline in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such a decline could decrease our gross profit and have a material adverse effect on our earnings and cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ing

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We depend on the accuracy and proper use of our management information systems, including our telephone system.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many of our key functions depend on the quality and effective utilization of the information generated by our management information systems, including:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our management information systems require continual upgrades to most effectively manage our operations and customer database.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although we maintain some redundant systems, with full data backup, our primary computer and telecommunications hardware is located in a single facility in New Hampshire, and a substantial interruption in our management information systems or in our telephone communication systems, including those resulting from extreme weather and natural disasters, as well as power loss, telecommunications failure, or similar events, would substantially hinder our ability to process customer orders and thus could have a material adverse effect on our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Should our financial performance not meet expectations and our stock price trade below current levels, we may be required to record a significant charge to earnings for impairment of goodwill
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	and other intangibles
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We test goodwill for impairment each year and more frequently if potential impairment indicators arise.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Although the fair value of our Large Account reporting unit substantially exceeded its carrying value at our annual impairment test, should
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the financial performance of the reporting unit not meet expectations due to the economy or otherwise, we would likely adjust downward its expected future operating results and cash flows.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such adjustment may result in a determination that the carrying value
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	goodwill
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and other intangibles
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the reporting unit exceeds its fair value.&nbsp;&nbsp;This determination may in turn require that we record a significant non-cash charge to earnings to reduce the $51.3 million aggregate carrying amount of goodwill held by our Large Account reporting unit, resulting in a negative effect on our results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	The failure to comply with our public sector contracts could result in, among other things, fines or liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Revenues from the Public S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ector segment are derived from sales to federal, state, and local government departments and agencies, as well as to educational institutions, through various contracts and open market sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Government contracting is a highly regulated area.&nbsp;&nbsp;Noncompliance with government procurement regulations or contract provisions could result in civil, criminal, and administrative liability, including substantial monetary fines or damages, termination of government contracts, and suspension, debarment, or ineligibility from doing business with the government.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our current arrangements with these government agencies allow them to cancel orders with little or no notice and do not require them to purchase products from us in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;The effect of any of these possible actions by any government department or agency could adversely affect our financial position, results of operations, and cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Substantially all of our contracts and arrangements with our vendors that supply significant quantities of products are terminable by such vendors or us without notice or upon short notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most of our product vendors provide us with trade credit, of which the net amount outstanding at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Termination, interruption, or contraction of relationships with our vendors, including a reduction in the level of trade credit provided to us, could have a material adverse effect on our financial position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Some product manufacturers either do not permit us to sell the full line of their products or limit the number of product units available to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	national solutions provider
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s such as us.&nbsp;&nbsp;An element of our business strategy is to continue increasing our participation in first-to-market purchase opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;The availability of certain desired products, especially in the direct marketing channel, has been constrained in the past.&nbsp;&nbsp;We could experience a material adverse effect to our business if we are unable to source first-to-market purchase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or similar opportunities, or if significant availability constraints
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	reoccur
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	We are exposed to inventory obsolescence due to the rapid technological changes occurring in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	industry.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The market for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products is characterized by rapid technological change and the frequent introduction of new products and product enhancements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our success depends in large part on our ability to identify and market products that meet the needs of customers in that marketplace.&nbsp;&nbsp;In order to satisfy customer demand and to obtain favorable purchasing discounts, we have and may continue to carry increased inventory levels of certain products.&nbsp;&nbsp;By so doing, we are subject to the increased risk of inventory obsolescence.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, in order to implement our business strategy, we intend to continue, among other things, placing larger than typical inventory stocking orders of selected products and increasing our participation in first-to-market purchase opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;We may also, from time to time, make large inventory purchases of certain end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;life products, which would increase the risk of inventory obsolescence.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, we sometimes acquire special purchase products without return privileges.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For these and other reasons, we may not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be able to avoid losses related to obsolete inventory.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	M
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	anufacturers have limited return rights and have taken steps to reduce their inventory exposure by supporting &#x201C;configure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to-order&#x201D; programs authorizing distributors and resellers to assemble computer hardware under the manufacturers&#x2019; brands.&nbsp;&nbsp;These actions reduce the costs to manufacturers and shift the burden of inventory risk to resellers like us, which could negatively impact our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	We are dependent on key personnel.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our future performance will depend to a significant extent upon the efforts and abilities of our senior executives and other key management personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;The competition for qualified management personnel in the computer products industry is very intense, and the loss of service of one or more of these persons could have an adverse effect on our business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our success and plans for future growth will also depend on our ability to hire, train, and retain skilled personnel in all areas of our business,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	especially
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales representatives and technical support personnel.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We may not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be able to attract, train, and retain sufficient qualified personnel to achieve our business objectives.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	The methods of distributing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	IT
</FONT>

	&nbsp;

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	use of rented or exchanged mailing lists
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	could negatively affect our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	We are controlled by two principal stockholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Patricia Gallup and David Hall, our two principal stockholders, beneficially own or control, in the aggregate,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the outstanding shares of our common stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because of their beneficial stock ownership, these stockholders can continue to elect the members of the Board of Directors and decide all matters requiring stockholder approval at a meeting or by a written consent in lieu of a meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Similarly, such stockholders can control decisions to adopt, amend, or repeal our charter and our bylaws, or take other actions requiring the vote or consent of our stockholders and prevent a takeover of us by one or more third parties, or sell or otherwise transfer their stock to a third party, which could deprive our stockholders of a control premium that might otherwise be realized by them in connection with an acquisition of our Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such control may result in decisions that are not in the best interest of our public stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with our initial public offering, the principal stockholders placed substantially all shares of common stock beneficially owned by them into a voting trust, pursuant to which they are required to agree as to the manner of voting such shares in order for the shares to be voted.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such provisions could discourage bids for our common stock at a premium as well as have a negative impact on the market price of our common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_RISK_FACTORS>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We lease our corporate headquarters located at 730 Milford Road, Merrimack, New Hampshire 03054-4631, from an affiliated company, G&amp;H Post, which is related to us through common ownership.&nbsp;&nbsp;The initial term of the fifteen-year lease ended November 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	to extend the term for an additional five years.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to the rent payable under the facility lease, we are required to pay real estate taxes, insurance, and common area maintenance charges.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The amended lease has been recorded as an operating lease in the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an option to renew the lease for two additional two-year terms, at the then comparable market rate.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	parties and also to pay insurance premiums for the leased property.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease has been recorded as an operating lease in the financial statements.

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4

<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 7.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
</FONT>
<A NAME="PCCC-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM7MANAGEMENTSDISCUSSIONANDANALYSISOFF">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our management&#x2019;s discussion and analysis of our financial condition and results of operations include the identification of certain trends and other statements that may predict or anticipate future business or financial results that are subject to important factors that could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated.&nbsp;&nbsp;See &#x201C;Item 1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Factors.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	OVERVIEW
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are a national solutions provider of a wide range of information technology, or IT, solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;We help our customers design, enable, manage, and service their IT environments. We provide IT products, including computer systems, software and peripheral equipment, networking communications, and other products and accessories that we purchase from manufacturers, distributors, and other suppliers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also offer services involving design, configuration, and implementation of IT solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;These services are performed by our personnel and by third-party providers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We operate through three sales segments, which serve primarily: (a) small- to medium-sized businesses, or SMBs, through our PC Connection Sales subsidiary, (b) large enterprise customers, in our Large Account segment, through our MoreDirect subsidiary, and (c) federal, state, and local government and educational institutions, in our Public Sector segment, through our GovConnection subsidiary.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We generate sales primarily through outbound telemarketing and field sales contacts by account managers focused on the business, education, and government markets, our websites, and inbound calls from customers responding to our catalogs and other advertising media.&nbsp;&nbsp;We seek to recruit, retain, and increase the productivity of our sales personnel through training, mentoring, financial incentives based on performance, and updating and streamlining our information systems to make our operations more efficient.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a value added reseller in the IT supply chain, we do not manufacture IT hardware or software.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are dependent on our suppliers&#x2014;manufacturers and distributors that historically have sold only to resellers rather than directly to end users.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, certain manufacturers have on multiple occasions attempted to sell directly to our customers, and in some cases, have restricted our ability to sell their products directly to certain customers, thereby attempting to eliminate our role.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that the success of these direct sales efforts by suppliers will depend on their ability to meet our customers&#x2019; ongoing demands and provide objective, unbiased solutions to meet their needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe more of our customers are seeking comprehensive IT solutions, rather than simply the acquisition of specific IT products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our advantage is our ability to be product-neutral and provide a broader combination of products, services, and advice tailored to customer needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;By providing customers with customized solutions from a variety of manufacturers, we believe we can mitigate the negative impact of continued direct sales initiatives from individual manufacturers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Through the formation of our ProConnection services group we are able to provide customers complete IT solutions, from identifying their needs, to designing, developing, and managing the integration of products and services to implement their IT projects.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such service offerings carry higher margins than traditional product sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the technical certifications of our service engineers permit us to offer higher-end, more complex products that generally carry higher gross margins.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect these service offerings and technical certifications to continue to play a role in sales generation and improve gross margins in this competitive environment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The primary challenges we continue to face in effectively managing our business are (1) increasing our revenues while at the same time improving our gross margin in all three segments, (2) recruiting, retaining, and improving the productivity of our sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and technical support
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	personnel, and (3) effectively controlling our selling, general, and administrative, or SG&amp;A, expenses while making major investments in our IT systems and solution selling personnel, especially in relation to changing revenue levels.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To support future growth, we are expanding our IT solution business, which requires the addition of highly-skilled service engineers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although we expect to realize the ultimate benefit of higher-margin service revenues under this multi-year initiative, we believe that our cost of services will increase significantly as we add service engineers.&nbsp;&nbsp;If our service revenues do not grow enough to offset the cost of these headcount additions, our operating results may decline.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	21
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#PCCC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Market conditions and technology advances significantly affect the demand for our products and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;Virtual delivery of software products and advanced Internet technology providing customers enhanced functionality have substantially increased customer expectations, requiring us to invest more heavily in our own IT development to meet these new demands.&nbsp;&nbsp;This investment includes significant planned expenditures to update our websites, as buying trends change and electronic commerce continues to grow.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our investments in IT infrastructure are designed to enable us to operate more efficiently and provide our customers enhanced functionality.&nbsp;&nbsp;While we have not yet finalized our decisions regarding the areas of future investment in our IT infrastructure, we expect to increase our capital investments in our IT infrastructure in the next three to five years, which will also likely increase SG&amp;A expenses as assets are placed into service and depreciated.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$110.6 million, or 4.5%, compared
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, due
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	primarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our Large Account
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net sales of notebooks/mobility products increased as mobility continued to be a strategic focus for customers in all three segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our investments in advanced solution sales also led to increased sales of software and servers/storage products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Gross margin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(gross profit expressed as a percentage of net sales)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increased slightly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	compared to the prior
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	year.&nbsp;&nbsp;SG&amp;A expenses
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	remained unchanged
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as a percentage of net sales, but
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increased in dollars due to incremental variable compensation associated with higher gross profits and investments in sol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ution sales and support personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating income in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015 increased year over year in both dollars and as a percentage of net sales due to the increase in net sales.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net sales for the Large Account segment increased due to our focus on growing advanced solution sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	including software and servers/storage products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Software and servers/storage product sales for this segment increased year over year by 27% and 14%, respectively, due to our investment in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	technical solution engineers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and the completion of large software deals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Servers sales increased in part due to the expiration in July 2015 of support for Windows Server 2003 software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net sales to the Public Sector segment decreased by 0.4% or $2.5 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sales to the federal government increased by 8.7% due to higher sales made under federal government contracts, while state and local government and educational institutions decreased by 4.0% due to lower sales to K-12 customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sales of notebooks/mobility increased in this segment, offset by decreased sales of net/com products.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Gross profit for the SMB segment increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	due to an increase in net sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and gross margin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Gross margin increased year over year due to higher invoice selling margins (29 basis points) realized on increased sales of higher-margin net/com and storage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	products, as well as an increase in vendor early-payment discounts (9 basis points).

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	segment increased due to higher net sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Gross margin decreased due to lower invoice selling margins (41 basis points) associated with increased sales of lower-margin notebooks/mobility products, offset by higher agency revenues (16 basis points).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;We receive agency fees from suppliers for certain software and hardware sales which are recorded as revenue with no corresponding cost of goods sold, and accordingly such fees have a positive impact on gross margin.

	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our tax rate will vary based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	income apportionment to certain jurisdictions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, valuation reserves, and accounting for uncertain tax positions.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, we do not expect these variations to be significant in 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	increased by $4.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to $46.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	from $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	42.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, principally due to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	increase in operating income.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Liquidity Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our primary sources of liquidity have historically been internally generated funds from operations and borrowings under our bank line of credit.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have used those funds to meet our capital requirements, which consist primarily of working capital for operational needs, capital expenditures for computer equipment and software used in our business, repurchases of common stock for treasury, dividend payments, and as opportunities arise, possible acquisitions of new businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our ability to continue funding our planned growth, both internally and externally, is dependent upon our ability to generate sufficient cash flow from operations or to obtain additional funds through equity or debt financing, or from other sources of financing, as may be required.&nbsp;&nbsp;While we do not anticipate needing any additional sources of financing to fund our operations at this time, if demand for IT products declines, our cash flows from operations may be substantially affected.&nbsp;&nbsp;See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	also related risks listed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	under &#x201C;Item 1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Factors.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

	2015

	resulted primarily from net income before depreciation and amortization

	and an increase in accounts payable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	offset partially by increases in accounts receivable and inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accounts receivable increased year over year by $64.2 million primarily due to the timing of sales at the end of 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;D

	ays sales outstanding

	0

	2015

	&nbsp;

	due primarily to an increase in purchases made to address increased future demand. Inventory days, which is the m

	easure of the average number of days goods remain in inventory before being sold, increased from 1

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$166.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in outstanding accounts payable.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such accounts are generally paid within 30 days of incurrence, or earlier when favorable cash discounts are offered.&nbsp;&nbsp;This balance will be financed by cash flows from operations or short-term borrowings under the line of credit.&nbsp;&nbsp;This amount includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$23.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million payable to two financial institutions under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	inventory trade credit agreements we use to finance our purchase of certain inventory, secured by the inventory which is financed.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We believe we will be able to meet our obligations under our accounts payable with cash flows from operations and our existing line of credit.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cash used for investing activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increased $5.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	compared to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Cash used to purchase property and equipment less proceeds from the sale of equipment amounted to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$12.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015, compared to $7.6 million in 2014 and 2013, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;These expenditures were primarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	capitalized internally-developed software in connection with the investments in our IT infrastructure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and in 2015, included our investment in a distribution center
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	&nbsp;

	provided by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	financing activities

	in
</FONT>

	creased $10
</FONT>

	.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in

	2015

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, compared to

	2014

	.

	&nbsp; &nbsp;

	Cash provided by f
</FONT>

	inancing
</FONT>

</FONT>

	uses of cash included dividends of

	$10.5 million

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Debt Instruments, Contractual Agreements, and Related Covenants
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Below is a summary of certain provisions of our credit facilities and other contractual obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;For more information about the restrictive covenants in our debt instruments and inventory financing agreements, see &#x201C;Factors Affecting Sources of Liquidity&#x201D; below.&nbsp;&nbsp;For more information about our obligations, commitments, and contingencies, see our consolidated financial statements and the accompanying notes included in this annual report.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Bank Line of Credit.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Our bank line of credit extends until February 2017 and is collateralized by our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accounts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	receivable.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our borrowing capacity is up to $50.0 million at the one-month London Interbank Offered Rate, or LIBOR, plus a spread based on our funded debt ratio, or in the absence of LIBOR, the prime rate (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.50% at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	).&nbsp;&nbsp;The one-month LIBOR rate at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3%.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we have the option to increase the facility by an additional $30.0 million to meet additional borrowing requirements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our credit facility is subject to certain covenant requirements which are described below under &#x201C;Factors Affecting Sources of Liquidity.&#x201D;&nbsp;&nbsp;We did not have any borrowings under the credit facility during the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cash receipts are automatically applied against any outstanding borrowings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any excess cash on account may either remain on account to generate earned credits to offset up to 100% of cash management fees, or may be invested in short-term qualified investments.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrowings under the line of credit are classified as current.&nbsp;&nbsp;At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the entire $50.0 million facility was available for borrowing. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Trade Credit Agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have additional security agreements with two financial institutions to facilitate the purchase of inventory from various suppliers under certain terms and conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;These agreements allow a collateralized first position in certain branded products in our inventory that were financed by these two institutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although the agreements provide for up to 100% financing on the purchase price of these products, up to an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$65.0 million, any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	outstanding financing must be fully secured by available inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;We do not pay any interest or discount fees on such inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;The related costs are borne by the suppliers as an incentive for us to purchase their products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Amounts outstanding under such facilities, which equaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$23.0 million in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the aggregate as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, are recorded in accounts payable.&nbsp;&nbsp;The inventory financed is classified as inventory on the consolidated balance sheet.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Bank Line of Credit.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Our bank line of credit extends until February 2017 and is collateralized by our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accounts receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the entire $50.0 million facility was available for borrowing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our credit facility contains certain financial ratios and operational covenants and other restrictions (including restrictions on additional debt, guarantees, and other distributions, investments, and liens) with which we and all of our subsidiaries must comply.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any failure to comply with these covenants would constitute a default and could prevent us from borrowing additional funds under this line of credit.&nbsp;&nbsp;This credit facility contains two financial tests:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The funded debt ratio (defined as the average outstanding advances under the line for the quarter, divided by the consolidated Adjusted EBITDA for the trailing four quarters) must not be more than 2.0 to 1.0.&nbsp;&nbsp;We did not have any outstanding borrowings under the credit facility during the fourth quarter of
